docs.abstract: With attendance down, some auto museums that were once prime attractions have closed their doors.
docs.snippet: With attendance down, some auto museums that were once prime attractions have closed their doors.
docs.lead_paragraph: LAS VEGAS — On the final day of move-out for the Auto Collections at the Linq Hotel & Casino, Rob Williams sat at a lonely wooden desk on one end of 125,000 square feet of emptiness. The only trace of the hundreds of cars that have passed through here over nearly 40 years were the oil stains on the carpet and walls adorned with the painted logos of the manufacturers whose wares were once among this tourist city’s most popular daytime attractions.

headline.main: In the Car Museum Race, Some Drop Out
headline.print_headline: Classic Car Museums Are Losing Much of Their Luster

docs.abstract: A new Pew report says banks and credit unions could help consumers who need fast cash. “Borrowers need a better option,” a Pew official says.
docs.snippet: A new Pew report says banks and credit unions could help consumers who need fast cash. “Borrowers need a better option,” a Pew official says.
docs.lead_paragraph: Those who find themselves pinched for cash often turn to high-cost payday lenders. But traditional banks and credit unions could serve that role for borrowers and do it at much lower rates, according to a new proposal from the Pew Charitable Trusts.

headline.main: Banks Urged to Take On Payday Lenders With Small, Lower-Cost Loans
headline.print_headline: Banks Urged to Offer Loans To Payday Borrowers

docs.abstract: Some companies are moving manufacturing to the United States, even as petitions for exemptions continue. But the rate of installations has slowed.

docs.lead_paragraph: SunPower is the nation’s No. 2 commercial solar-power company, employing thousands of workers directly and indirectly. But it makes most of its solar panels abroad, and with the tariffs recently imposed by President Trump costing it as much as $2 million a week, SunPower is fighting for an exemption.

headline.main: Trump’s Solar Tariffs Cause a Scramble in the Industry
